      "span_text": "The formal 6 A recent retrospective article honoring the twenty-fifth anniversary of the publication of Olson's Rise and Decline highlighted the \"distinction between distributional coalitions, which are seen as leading to outcomes inimical to economic growth, and encompassing coalitions, which are seen as potentially aiding economic growth …\" as the first of the book's two \"crucial innovations\" [CITATION_1] ."
